# .easignore — controls what EAS Build uploads to its workers.
#
# EAS uploads the whole SDK repo here because Examples/expo links the SDK via
# `file:../..`, so the build context is this repo root. EAS uses .easignore
# INSTEAD of .gitignore for the archive, so the build-output entries from
# .gitignore are restated below — and additionally we drop a large block of
# accidentally-tracked Xcode build cache (example/ios/derived/, ~550 MB).
#
# Do NOT ignore the SDK source (src/, plugin/, ios/, android/, nitrogen/,
# package.json, *.podspec, app.plugin.js, react-native.config.js) or
# Examples/expo — the build needs them. The example apps stay present as
# workspace members; only their build outputs are excluded.
#
# EXCEPTION: Examples/expo is a CNG (Continuous Native Generation) app — its
# ios/ and android/ are gitignored and meant to be regenerated by `expo
# prebuild` on the EAS worker. They are excluded below so a local prebuild's
# output is never uploaded; otherwise EAS detects the native dirs, bare-builds
# them, and SKIPS prebuild (stale native code, wrong signing/env — a dev
# profile can yield a production APNs token — and committed Config Plugin
# fixes are not applied).

# --- node / dependencies (restated from .gitignore) ---
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.yalc/
npm-debug.log
yarn-debug.log
yarn-error.log

# --- JS build output (restated from .gitignore) ---
lib/
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# --- native build output (restated from .gitignore) ---
build/
DerivedData/
xcuserdata
*.xcuserstate
*.hmap
*.ipa
.gradle
**/Pods/
example/ios/Pods/
example/vendor/
android/app/libs

# --- accidentally-tracked Xcode build cache (~550 MB, pure build artifact) ---
# example/ios/derived/ is committed to the repo; excluded here for upload.
# See repo-hygiene follow-up to untrack it.
**/derived/
*.pcm

# --- Expo sample CNG native dirs — force EAS to prebuild, not bare-build ---
# Gitignored generated folders. Anchored (leading path) so the SDK's own
# ios/ and android/ are NOT matched — only Examples/expo's generated output.
Examples/expo/ios/
Examples/expo/android/

# --- tooling / editor / VCS ---
.expo/
.vscode/
.idea/
.git/
.DS_Store
